==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: harlequin snake
<hw>har"le*quin snake`</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>any of several venomous
New World snakes brilliantly banded in red and black and either yellow
or white, especially the <stype>eastern coral snake</stype>, a small
poisonous snake (<spn>Micrurus fulvius</spn> or <spn>Elaps
fulvius</spn>), ringed with red and black, found in the Southeastern
United States. They are widely distributed in Southern and Central
America;</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> coral snake, New World coral snake.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Harlock</ent>⟦br⟧
